## ☕ Coffee Classes (Decorator Pattern)

### Why Decorator Pattern?
- Users can **customize** their coffee (add extra sugar, milk)
- Each addition adds to the **cost** and **description**
- Decorators **wrap** the base coffee and modify behavior

### Class Hierarchy

```
        ┌─────────────────┐
        │  Coffee (ABC)   │
        ├─────────────────┤
        │ + get_cost()    │
        │ + get_desc()    │
        │ + get_recipe()  │
        └────────┬────────┘
                 │
    ┌────────────┼────────────┐
    │            │            │
┌───▼───┐   ┌────▼────┐   ┌───▼────┐
│Espresso│   │  Latte  │   │Cappuccino│
│  ₹30   │   │   ₹40   │   │   ₹50   │
└────────┘   └─────────┘   └─────────┘

        ┌─────────────────────┐
        │ CoffeeDecorator(ABC)│ ◄── Also extends Coffee
        ├─────────────────────┤
        │ - wrapped: Coffee   │
        │ + get_cost()        │
        │ + get_desc()        │
        └────────┬────────────┘
                 │
        ┌────────┴────────┐
        │                 │
┌───────▼──────┐  ┌───────▼──────┐
│SugarDecorator│  │ MilkDecorator│
│    +₹5       │  │    +₹10      │
└──────────────┘  └──────────────┘
```

### Coffee (Abstract Base)

| Attribute/Method | Type | Description |
|------------------|------|-------------|
| `get_cost()` | Abstract | Return total cost |
| `get_description()` | Abstract | Return drink name |
| `get_recipe()` | Abstract | Return {Ingredient: amount} |

### Espresso (Concrete Coffee)

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Cost | ₹30 |
| Recipe | {COFFEE: 2, WATER: 1, SUGAR: 1} |
| Description | "Espresso" |

### Latte (Concrete Coffee)

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Cost | ₹40 |
| Recipe | {COFFEE: 1, MILK: 2, WATER: 1, SUGAR: 1} |
| Description | "Latte" |

### Cappuccino (Concrete Coffee)

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Cost | ₹50 |
| Recipe | {COFFEE: 1, MILK: 1, WATER: 1, SUGAR: 2} |
| Description | "Cappuccino" |

### CoffeeDecorator (Abstract Decorator)

| Attribute | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| `_wrapped_coffee` | Coffee | The coffee being decorated |
| `get_cost()` | Method | Returns wrapped cost + own cost |
| `get_description()` | Method | Returns wrapped desc + own desc |

### SugarDecorator (Concrete Decorator)

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Extra Cost | ₹5 |
| Extra Recipe | {SUGAR: 1} |
| Description | " + Extra Sugar" |

### MilkDecorator (Concrete Decorator)

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Extra Cost | ₹10 |
| Extra Recipe | {MILK: 1} |
| Description | " + Extra Milk" |

### How Decoration Works

```python
# User orders Latte with extra sugar and milk
coffee = Latte()                    # ₹40, "Latte"
coffee = SugarDecorator(coffee)     # ₹45, "Latte + Extra Sugar"
coffee = MilkDecorator(coffee)      # ₹55, "Latte + Extra Sugar + Extra Milk"

print(coffee.get_cost())        # 55
print(coffee.get_description()) # "Latte + Extra Sugar + Extra Milk"
```

