## 🔄 Machine States (State Pattern)

### Why State Pattern?
- Machine behavior depends on current state
- Each state has different valid actions
- Transitions are explicit and controlled

### State Diagram

```
         ┌──────────────┐
         │   IDLE       │ ◄── Machine waiting, display menu
         └──────┬───────┘
                │ selectCoffee()
                ▼
    ┌───────────────────────┐
    │   AWAITING_PAYMENT    │ ◄── Waiting for coins
    └───────────┬───────────┘
                │ insertCoin() until amount >= price
                ▼
         ┌──────────────┐
         │  DISPENSING  │ ◄── Making coffee
         └──────┬───────┘
                │ dispense complete
                ▼
         ┌──────────────┐
         │    IDLE      │ ◄── Ready for next customer
         └──────────────┘
```

### MachineState (Abstract)

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `select_coffee(machine, coffee)` | Handle coffee selection |
| `insert_coin(machine, coin)` | Handle coin insertion |
| `dispense(machine)` | Handle dispensing |
| `cancel(machine)` | Handle cancellation |

### IdleState

| Action | Behavior |
|--------|----------|
| `select_coffee()` | ✅ Check availability, transition to AWAITING_PAYMENT |
| `insert_coin()` | ❌ "Please select a coffee first" |
| `dispense()` | ❌ "Please select a coffee first" |
| `cancel()` | ❌ "Nothing to cancel" |

### AwaitingPaymentState

| Action | Behavior |
|--------|----------|
| `select_coffee()` | ❌ "Coffee already selected" |
| `insert_coin()` | ✅ Add to total. If enough, transition to DISPENSING |
| `dispense()` | ❌ "Please complete payment first" |
| `cancel()` | ✅ Refund inserted amount, return to IDLE |

### DispensingState

| Action | Behavior |
|--------|----------|
| `select_coffee()` | ❌ "Please wait, dispensing" |
| `insert_coin()` | ❌ "Please wait, dispensing" |
| `dispense()` | ✅ Make coffee, deduct ingredients, return to IDLE |
| `cancel()` | ❌ "Cannot cancel, already dispensing" |

